The paper proposes a deep learning model for classifying histologic patterns in lung adenocarcinoma on surgical resection slides. This task involves image analysis and classification, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL) sub-categories. The model also uses convolutional neural networks, which is a common technique in deep learning for image analysis. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques for text analysis of pathology reports, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR).
